x² + 3x - 4

Solution
The numerator factors as (x + 4) (x - 1), so the x-intercepts are -4 and 1. The zero
of the denominator x - 2 is 2, so x = 2 is a vertical asymptote.
The degree of the numerator, 2, is greater than the degree of the denominator, 1,
so the graph has no horizontal asymptote. The graph has the same end behavior
as the graph of y=x²-1 = x. Plot points on each side of the vertical asymptote.
